    "Exodus & Leviticus": ").\nVer.\n27. And Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]` let his father in law depart, etc.] After he had been\nwith him some time, and desired leave to go into his own country, which\nwas granted; or he \u201cdismissed\u201d f578 him in an honourable way: and as he\nwent out to meet him when he came, if he did not attend him, when he\nwent, some way in person, yet sent a guard along with him, both for\nhonour and for safety:\nand he went his way into his own land; the land of Midian: the Targum of\nJonathan,\n\u201che went to proselyte all the children of his own country;\u201d\nor, as Jarchi expresses it, the children of his family; and it is plain that the\nKenites and Rechabites descended from him, who in later times lived\n[v_Jdg_1_16] among the Jews, and were proselytes to their religion, (<070116>Judges 1:16\n[v_1Ch_2_55] <130255>1 Chronicles 2:55 <243502>Jeremiah 35:2).\n289\n27. Give substance and result of the first interview between Pharaoh and Moses `[char_Moses_Exo_2]`?"
